column5: Hadn't been up to camp in a while, so we had to go in to close it up... see you in the spring.. sniff sniff.. hopefully we will get up more next year!!  It snowed about 8 inches while we were in... made getting out with the four wheelers abit dicey!!        Cant wait to get back up thee in the spring!!
What were the temps like in the spa?
The spas was hot as always... bout the only warm place....
Good to hear at least you brought the "woodsplitter" with you.   Art
Jiggy jiggy is lookin better all the time tj !!! Minus the snow and the closing it up of course !!! I feel the same way when I put the boat away for her long winter sleep !!! Sniff,sniff ..... Lol

TJ, I feel your pain. We are heading up to close the cottage this weekend. I serviced and put the boat away 2 weeks ago and now it is the cottage's turn. Now to look forward to March break for re opening and May for splashing the boat again. Absence makes the heart grow fonder.........
